<TITLE> Project to cut crude transport time okayed </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 11 (bdnews24.com)The government has approved a project that would cut time required to transport crude from containers to the Eastern Refineries down to 48 hours at most from at least 11 days. The Single Point Mooring project in deep sea near Kutubdia will save both time and wastage as this would virtually eliminate the usage of lighterage vessels and lorries for transporting crude and oil from containers ships to the Eastern Refineries in Chittagong. The project was approved at a meeting of the Executive Committee of the National Economic Council headed by prime minister Sheikh Hasina on Tuesda
